System requirements:
Processor: minimum 1 GHz, recommended at least 2GHz

HDD: at least 20 GB
Video card: DirectX v. 9 compatible or better
Description: A major Windows 10 update also known as Redstone 4, version 1803, PRO Edition. This update includes the following: Timeline (recent apps screen for your devices), HDR video support, Microsoft Edge improvements, quick pairing of Bluetooth devices, Nearby Share, etc. Moreover, this build also includes integrated Google Chrome, Avast Antivirus and Activator.
How to write the image on a USB flash drive using UltraIso
1) Install and launch UltraIso application
2) In the File menu, click Open, select the downloaded Windows image and press Open.
3) Make sure you have opened the image. In the Bootable menu click on Write disk image.
4) In the drop-down list Disk Drive, select your USB flash drive. In the drop-down list Write Method, select USB-HDD+ and click the Write button.
5) A window will appear informing that all the information on the USB flash drive will be deleted. Press Yes. Wait until the procedure is completed (it can take 5 to 20 minutes depending on the writing speed of the drive).
6) Restart your computer without removing the USB flash drive from the USB port. Immediately after your computer begins restarting, open enter the BIOS firmware by pressing the Delete (Del) or F2 key depending on BIOS version. In the BIOS, change the priority of booting devices and make the USB-HDD the primary booting device.
7) Save changes and exit BIOS. The computer will restart again, this time booting from the flash drive.
How to activate your system
You can activate the OS using the built-in Activator by clicking on the corresponding icon on the desktop. During activation, you will be asked to grant permission for adding reactivation to the schedule.
